{
  "accession": "PXD000475",
  "title": "Yersinia enterocolitica SOR17 -  The RNA chaperone Hfq impacts growth, metabolism and production of virulence factors in Yersinia enterocolitica",
  "additionalAttributes": [],
  "projectDescription": "We work with the bacterium Yersinia enterocolitica, a gastrointestinal pathogen.  In this study we characterized a bacterial mutant strain called SOR17.  We compared the protein extracts of SOR17 with that of the parental strain JB580v.  Bacteria were grown in triplicate for 5 h at 37°C, and following bacterial disruption by French press, proteins were fractionated into soluble or membrane proteins.  We also compared total protein extracts of bacteria grown for 16 h at 27°C. Two-dimensional electrophoresis were performed and proteins were stained with Coomassie brilliant blue.  Spots whose abundance changed more than 2 fold were excised and sent to mass spectrometry for identification by either MALDI-TOF PMF or LC-MS/MS.",
